'''加利福尼亚州22号提案 (2020年)'''（英语: Proposition 22，简称 Prop 22），全称为“'''豁免基于[[行動應用程式|应用程序]]的运输公司和快递公司向特定驾驶员提供员工福利”''' ，是一项美国[[加利福尼亚州|加利福尼亚州]]的[[公投|公投]]提案，该提案在2020年11月3日的大选獲得通過。 <ref name=":0">{{Cite news |author= |first= |title=加州選民挺Uber、Lyft 支持司機歸類承攬關係 |url=https://news.ltn.com.tw/news/world/breakingnews/3342115 |accessdate= |work=自由時報 |date=2020年11月4日 |archive-date=2020年11月20日 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201120142354/https://news.ltn.com.tw/news/world/breakingnews/3342115 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

该提案将基于应用程序的运输公司和快递公司之驾驶员定义为“独立承包商”，而非“员工”，以豁免這些公司按照 AB-5 法案（英文：{{tsl|en|California Assembly Bill 5 (2019)|Assembly Bill 5}}）向驾驶员提供员工福利。<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|title=Uber and Lyft just made their campaign to keep exploiting workers|url=https://www.latimes.com/business/story/2020-09-08/uber-lyft-most-expensive-initiative|accessdate=2020-10-14|author=Hiltzik|date=8 September 2020|first=Michael|work=[[Los_Angeles_Times|Los Angeles Times]]|language=en-US|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20201104231642/https://www.latimes.com/business/story/2020-09-08/uber-lyft-most-expensive-initiative|archivedate=2020-11-04|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=":2">{{Cite news|author=|first=|date=31 October 2019|title=Uber and Lyft Fight a Law They Say Doesn't Apply to Them|language=en-us|work=Wired|url=https://www.wired.com/story/uber-lyft-fight-law-say-doesnt-apply/|accessdate=2020-10-14|archive-date=2020-12-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201214163025/https://www.wired.com/story/uber-lyft-fight-law-say-doesnt-apply/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

该提案还为這些运输公司和快递公司的驾驶员提供了额外的劳动保护措施，但大多数保护措施仅在“从事”超过特定时间后才适用，而非登录应用程序后即适用。<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-07-07/uber-lyft-ballot-measure-opposed-by-labor-groups |title=California’s Gig Economy Ballot Measure Fails Workers, Labor Groups Say |last1=Holder |first1=Sarah |date=7 July 2020 |website=bloomberg.com |publisher=Bloomberg |accessdate=18 October 2020 |archive-date=2020-10-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201024014842/https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-07-07/uber-lyft-ballot-measure-opposed-by-labor-groups |dead-url=no }}</ref>

[[来福车|Lyft]]、[[優步|Uber]]、DoorDash、Instacart和Postmates已为支持22号提案的竞选活动提供了超过1.8亿美元的政治献金，使其成为加州历史上最“昂贵”的公投提案。 <ref name=":3">{{Cite news|url=https://news.ballotpedia.org/2020/09/09/with-funding-from-uber-lyft-and-doordash-campaign-behind-california-proposition-22-tops-180-million/|title=With funding from Uber, Lyft, and Doordash, campaign behind California Proposition 22 tops $180 million|author=Byrne|first=Ryan|date=9 September 2020|work=ballotpedia.org|publisher=Ballotpedia|accessdate=10 September 2020|archive-date=2020-11-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201119010720/https://news.ballotpedia.org/2020/09/09/with-funding-from-uber-lyft-and-doordash-campaign-behind-california-proposition-22-tops-180-million/|dead-url=no}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|title=The $185 million campaign to keep Uber and Lyft drivers as contractors in California|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/10/08/tech/proposition-22-california/index.html|accessdate=2020-10-14|author=O'Brien|first=Sara Ashley|work=CNN|archive-date=2020-12-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201214204131/https://www.cnn.com/2020/10/08/tech/proposition-22-california/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>其中包括为“对议案22投赞成票”广告<ref>{{Cite web|title=Yes on Prop 22|url=https://yeson22.com/|accessdate=2020-10-14|author=|date=|first=|work=Save App-Based Jobs & Services|language=en-US|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20201104011456/https://yeson22.com/|archivedate=2020-11-04|quote=Paid for by Yes on 22 […] Committee major funding from Uber Technologies, Lyft, and DoorDash.|dead-url=no}}</ref>提供大量投放资金，以及在它们的应用程序中向客户推广该提案。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Uber, Lyft push Prop. 22 message where you can't escape it: your phone|url=https://www.latimes.com/business/technology/story/2020-10-08/uber-lyft-novel-tactics-huge-spending-prop-22|accessdate=2020-10-14|date=2020-10-08|work=Los Angeles Times|language=en-US|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20201221034331/https://www.latimes.com/business/technology/story/2020-10-08/uber-lyft-novel-tactics-huge-spending-prop-22|archivedate=2020-12-21|dead-url=no}}</ref> <ref name=":4">{{Cite web|title=Uber and Lyft get reprieve from court, won't shut down in California for now|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/08/20/tech/uber-lyft-california-shutdown/index.html|accessdate=2020-10-14|author=O'Brien|date=|first=Sara Ashley|work=CNN|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20201216124508/https://www.cnn.com/2020/08/20/tech/uber-lyft-california-shutdown/index.html|archivedate=2020-12-16|quote=[…], the companies have threatened to suspend their services, and sometimes followed through on it, riling up customers and drivers, and putting pressure on lawmakers.|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 背景 ==
2019 年, 加利福尼亚州 AB-5 法案确认，被归类为"员工"的劳工有权获得劳动保护措施（包括最低工资和病假）<ref>{{Cite web|date=2019-09-18|title=Newsom signs bill rewriting California employment law, limiting use of independent contractors|url=https://www.latimes.com/california/story/2019-09-18/gavin-newsom-signs-ab5-employees0independent-contractors-california|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201221034324/https://www.latimes.com/california/story/2019-09-18/gavin-newsom-signs-ab5-employees0independent-contractors-california|archive-date=2020-12-21|access-date=2020-10-14|website=Los Angeles Times|language=en-US|dead-url=no}}</ref> 该法案扩大了“员工”的定义范围，将原本属于“独立承包商”的劳工纳入“员工”范围。此举将使得派遣司机和其它[[零工经济|零工经济]]参与者被视为"员工"。<ref name=":2" /> Lyft和Uber表示希望司机会被继续归类为"独立承包商"。<ref name=":1" /><ref name=":3" /><ref>{{Cite web|title=Human Capital: A timeline of Uber and Lyft’s fight against AB 5 and Pinterest’s fall from grace|url=https://social.techcrunch.com/2020/08/14/human-capital-a-timeline-of-uber-and-lyfts-fight-against-ab-5-and-pinterests-fall-from-grace/|access-date=2020-10-14|website=TechCrunch|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Spangler|first=Todd|date=2020-08-21|title=Why Uber and Lyft Were on the Brink of Shutting Down in California — and What Happens Next|url=https://variety.com/2020/digital/news/uber-lyft-california-shutdown-ab5-1234743303/|access-date=2020-10-14|website=Variety|language=en|archive-date=2020-11-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201103185753/https://variety.com/2020/digital/news/uber-lyft-california-shutdown-ab5-1234743303/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2020年8月，加利福尼亚法庭命令Uber和Lyft必须在10天内遵守AB-5法案的规定。<ref>{{Cite web|last=O'Brien|first=Sara Ashley|title=Court orders Uber, Lyft to reclassify drivers as employees in California|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/08/10/tech/uber-lyft-california-preliminary-injunction/index.html|access-date=2020-10-14|website=CNN|archive-date=2020-10-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201029115406/https://www.cnn.com/2020/08/10/tech/uber-lyft-california-preliminary-injunction/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref> 这两家公司其后声称，如果他们的{{Clarify span|一些驾驶员|date=October 2020}}要被归类"员工"，他们会关闭在加州的业务。<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":4">{{Cite web|last=O'Brien|first=Sara Ashley|date=|title=Uber and Lyft get reprieve from court, won't shut down in California for now|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/08/20/tech/uber-lyft-california-shutdown/index.html|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-10-14|website=CNN|quote=[…] , the companies have threatened to suspend their services, and sometimes followed through on it, riling up customers and drivers, and putting pressure on lawmakers.}}</ref>在8月20日，即法院命令的最后期限，两家公司要求延长执行期。法庭同意将最后期限延长至11月4日，但Uber和Lyft的CEO需要在10月4日前证明他们已有执行AB-5法案的相关计划。<ref name=":4" /><ref name=":0" /><ref name=":5">{{Cite web|last=Feiner|first=Lauren|date=2020-08-20|title=Appeals court grants Uber and Lyft a temporary reprieve following threats to shut down in California|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2020/08/20/appeals-court-grants-uber-and-lyft-a-temporary-reprieve-in-case-over-driver-classification.html|access-date=2020-10-14|website=CNBC|language=en|archive-date=2020-11-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201121090538/https://www.cnbc.com/2020/08/20/appeals-court-grants-uber-and-lyft-a-temporary-reprieve-in-case-over-driver-classification.html|dead-url=no}}</ref> 两家公司随后表示不会关闭其在加州的业务。<ref>{{Cite web|last=Inc|first=Lyft|date=|title=Rideshare operations will not be suspended in California|url=https://www.lyft.com/blog/posts/ca-operations-update|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200821001838/https://www.lyft.com/blog/posts/ca-operations-update|archive-date=2020-08-21|access-date=2020-10-14|website=Lyft|language=en-US|dead-url=no}}</ref>

